						<img alt='' src='http://2.gravatar.com/avatar/?s=56&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g' srcset='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/?s=112&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-56 photo avatar-default' height='56' width='56' />						<b class="fn"><a href='http://extemporanea.livejournal.com/' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>docinatrix</a></b> <span class="says">says:</span>					</div><!-- .comment-author -->

					<div class="comment-metadata">
						<a href="http://localhost:8888/microfiction.co.za/2010/10/17/gone/#comment-756">
							<time datetime="2010-11-01T13:10:35+00:00">
								November 1, 2010 at 1:10 pm							</time>
						</a>
											</div><!-- .comment-metadata -->

									</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>Thank you, glad you enjoyed it. I was a bit unsure about this one. Your confusions about tense noted, I think it&#8217;s part of the same duality elementalsystems picked up on &#8211; staying versus going, being part of the human race versus feeling differently, and past and present blur a little. FWIW, yes, I think the ice caps are slowly returning. </p>
<p>I disagree, however, on &#8220;temperatures&#8221;. &#8220;Now the skies are clear, the temperatures dropping&#8221; isn&#8217;t a misplaced contraction, it&#8217;s an elided verb construction in which temperatures are definitely plural. Its sense is actually &#8220;now the skies are clear, the temperatures [are] dropping&#8221;, I&#8217;ve just left out the second &#8220;are&#8221; for purposes of euphony. The omission is probably a highly technical grammatical construction with its own polysyllabic Greek name, such as I am totally abysmal at remembering even if it did happen to exist.</p>
				</div><!-- .comment-content -->

